column4: <content>N. Pevsner, BBC Lecture, 26-I-48 about 'Adoration of the Magi' by Bruegel: The Christ Childe cf. with Lazarus in Sebastiano del Piombo's Raising of Lazrus, The National Gallery; [toegevoegde vermelding]: ' F.G. 1) Query when did the Lazarus came to Narbonne? Was there any possibility for Bruegel to see the picture; 2) The motif of the child also in Titian's Pesaro Madonna (not in the child) especially the veil surrounding the child and drapping on the left side; 3) cf. also Raffael's Madonna di Foligno until 1565 High Altar of S. Maria in Aracoeli, Rome.</content>
<object.title>Doubtful & Wrong Attributions, Copies, Lost Pictures, nos. 43-46</object.title>
